WEBVTT

00:00.200 --> 00:01.399
Previously on "Heartland":

00:05.837 --> 00:08.606
Hey, you're okay.
You're okay.

00:08.674 --> 00:09.706
Amy Fleming.

00:09.774 --> 00:11.141
Stewart Forrest, Caesar's trainer.

00:11.208 --> 00:12.342
<i>He's an Olympic hopeful.</i>

00:12.410 --> 00:13.443
I mean, I don't know how you did that,

00:13.511 --> 00:15.178
but... thank you.

00:16.113 --> 00:17.514
You are not gonna believe this.

00:19.684 --> 00:21.151
Miracle girl?

00:21.218 --> 00:22.486
Fine. But you know I need you
to get back to me

00:22.553 --> 00:23.620
like yesterday.

00:25.822 --> 00:27.690
Trouble in Dubai?

00:27.758 --> 00:29.659
I'm having some cash flow issues.

00:29.726 --> 00:31.160
When chase said you couldn't
come to the movie,

00:31.227 --> 00:34.129
I should've just gone home.

00:34.197 --> 00:35.298
What movie?

00:35.365 --> 00:36.766
When you were studying, last night?

00:36.833 --> 00:38.033
I never meant...

00:38.101 --> 00:39.168
I didn't know that...

00:39.235 --> 00:40.636
Soraya.

00:40.704 --> 00:41.836
Chase.

00:41.904 --> 00:42.837
What?

00:42.905 --> 00:44.673
We can't do this.

00:44.740 --> 00:45.873
Do what?

00:45.941 --> 00:47.742
You're dating my best friend.

00:47.810 --> 00:48.876
And if I wasn't?

00:50.000 --> 00:56.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:23.711 --> 01:26.346
Well, look at that!

01:26.413 --> 01:29.148
You're famous.

01:29.216 --> 01:31.249
And a real nice picture too,

01:31.317 --> 01:33.184
don't you think?

01:33.252 --> 01:34.853
Oh, wow!

01:34.920 --> 01:36.087
That's pretty cool.

01:36.155 --> 01:37.956
Thanks.

01:38.023 --> 01:39.624
Off to school.
See you, guys.

01:39.692 --> 01:40.892
See ya.

01:40.960 --> 01:43.695
I am so proud of you.
You know that?

01:43.763 --> 01:45.330
Thank you.

01:45.997 --> 01:48.198
So, now, what are you doing
cleaning out Copper's stall?

01:48.266 --> 01:51.168
Well, Mallory sure isn't
showing up to do it.

01:51.236 --> 01:52.603
She hasn't called or anything?

01:52.671 --> 01:55.939
No. And I'm the one ends up
looking after her horse.

01:56.007 --> 01:59.577
You're, you're not too famous
to help me out, are you?

01:59.644 --> 02:01.111
Uh... no.

02:02.045 --> 02:03.045
Good.

02:03.113 --> 02:04.514
'Cause I wanna show this to Lou.

02:06.183 --> 02:08.485
Well, Stewart Forrest!
Good to see you.

02:08.551 --> 02:10.453
Hey! Stewart!

02:10.520 --> 02:11.788
Have you seen this?

02:11.856 --> 02:13.723
My Amy right there on the cover

02:13.791 --> 02:16.058
of <i>Western Financial Group</i> magazine.

02:16.126 --> 02:17.459
I did see it, yes.

02:17.527 --> 02:19.294
That's kind of why I'm here.

02:19.362 --> 02:20.962
It's been a while, miracle girl.

02:21.030 --> 02:22.598
- How have you been?
- Great!

02:22.665 --> 02:24.566
Good, 'cause I have a job for you.

02:24.634 --> 02:26.968
I need your help
with training someone.

02:27.036 --> 02:29.671
How could I possibly help you
with horse training?

02:29.739 --> 02:30.873
Oh, I think you can.

02:30.940 --> 02:32.007
You busy right now?

02:32.074 --> 02:34.241
Um...

02:34.309 --> 02:35.777
No.

02:35.844 --> 02:37.612
Then why don't you
come over to my barn

02:37.679 --> 02:39.346
and I'll show you.

02:39.415 --> 02:40.748
No-no, they can't!

02:40.816 --> 02:43.150
They can't do that.
We have it in writing.

02:44.620 --> 02:45.620
I thought we had people
representing us over there?

02:45.687 --> 02:46.921
Do we not?

02:46.988 --> 02:50.290
Are we not paying people
to represent us there?!

02:50.357 --> 02:52.158
What? No.
Are you crazy?

02:52.226 --> 02:53.393
I can't turn around

02:53.461 --> 02:54.628
and get on a plane back to Dubai.

02:54.695 --> 02:55.762
What am I gonna tell my wife?

02:57.899 --> 03:00.567
I gotta call you back.

03:00.635 --> 03:02.436
I will call you back.
Yes.

03:03.370 --> 03:05.171
What was that about?

03:05.239 --> 03:06.705
It's nothing.
It's Doug.

03:06.773 --> 03:07.973
You know, he doesn't feel
like he's ining his job

03:08.041 --> 03:09.775
unless everyone's having
a heart attack.

03:09.843 --> 03:10.910
You didn't have to end your call.

03:10.977 --> 03:12.344
I just wanted to show you something.

03:12.412 --> 03:15.380
Oh, honey, I'm happy
to get off the phone, honestly.

03:15.449 --> 03:17.516
- What's up?
- Look at this.

03:18.919 --> 03:19.985
Running strollers.

03:20.053 --> 03:21.586
Lightweight graphite composite,

03:21.654 --> 03:23.287
yet sturdy enough for gravel roads.

03:23.355 --> 03:25.490
Wow! it's...

03:25.558 --> 03:27.124
buy a small vehicle for that price.

03:27.192 --> 03:29.226
Yeah, they're a little more than some,

03:29.294 --> 03:31.362
- but you get what you pay for, right?
- Mm-hmm.

03:31.430 --> 03:32.964
I am not going to be
one of those mothers

03:33.031 --> 03:34.532
who carries around pregnancy pounds

03:34.600 --> 03:36.267
the next 15 years.

03:36.335 --> 03:37.935
You wouldn't want that, would you?

03:38.002 --> 03:39.670
Is there a right answer
to that question?

03:39.737 --> 03:41.171
So... the fit
or the summit?

03:42.540 --> 03:44.307
Uh... which one
comes with a motor?

03:44.375 --> 03:46.042
Well, Peter, just help me choose.

03:48.179 --> 03:49.446
Guys, look at this.

03:49.514 --> 03:51.548
Aww! Look at Amy!

03:52.484 --> 03:53.549
I have to head into town;

03:53.617 --> 03:55.250
I need a new pair of wire strippers.

03:55.318 --> 03:57.620
Amy's got my truck.
Can you give me a lift?

03:57.688 --> 03:58.855
I can do that.
No problem.

03:58.922 --> 04:00.990
- Uh... Peter?
- Yeah?

04:01.057 --> 04:02.391
Which stroller?

04:02.459 --> 04:03.526
Oh, honey, they're
ridiculously expensive.

04:03.594 --> 04:05.928
Let's figure something else out, okay?

04:08.064 --> 04:10.899
Two things a father
should not attempt:

04:10.967 --> 04:12.567
Teaching your daughter to drive

04:12.635 --> 04:16.004
and trying to coach her
before a big competition.

04:16.071 --> 04:17.005
Right, Riana?

04:17.072 --> 04:18.238
Right, dad.

04:18.307 --> 04:19.741
He's a really beautiful horse.

04:19.809 --> 04:20.909
Addison.

04:20.976 --> 04:22.477
Had my eye on him for two years

04:22.545 --> 04:25.079
and he finally became available.

04:25.147 --> 04:27.815
Paid too much for him
but he's worth it.

04:27.883 --> 04:31.184
<i>Look, Riana's got qualifiers
in a couple of weeks.</i>

04:31.252 --> 04:32.319
She's enthusiastic,

04:32.387 --> 04:33.621
wants to compete more than anything,

04:33.688 --> 04:37.725
but we never really found
the right horse for her until now.

04:37.792 --> 04:38.993
Wanna take him out for a spin?

04:39.060 --> 04:40.127
Yeah.

04:42.062 --> 04:43.229
Come on.

04:56.176 --> 04:57.709
She seems pretty tentative.

04:57.777 --> 04:59.377
<i>That's why I need your help.</i>

04:59.445 --> 05:01.046
See, Addison's the kind of animal

05:01.113 --> 05:03.148
that can really build the reputation

05:03.215 --> 05:04.850
of a young rider.

05:04.918 --> 05:07.352
He's too flat...
collect him up.

05:08.287 --> 05:10.221
That's a lot of horse for that girl,

05:10.289 --> 05:11.790
and a lot of bit.

05:11.858 --> 05:13.624
It's the only
way she can control him.

05:15.393 --> 05:16.627
Okay, sit back.

05:16.695 --> 05:18.095
<i>Sit back, drive!</i>

05:19.031 --> 05:20.531
<i>Drive!</i>

05:20.599 --> 05:21.966
- Watch... watch...

05:22.034 --> 05:24.068
Go around! Riana!

05:28.440 --> 05:30.239
You okay, honey?

05:31.876 --> 05:32.876
It's okay, I'm fine.

05:32.944 --> 05:34.410
You took a bit of a knock there.

05:34.478 --> 05:36.179
Oh, that was my fault.

05:36.246 --> 05:37.380
Riana,

05:37.448 --> 05:38.582
why don't you just take a break.

05:38.649 --> 05:40.817
Let him catch his breath, walk it out.

05:40.885 --> 05:42.452
Uh, okay.

05:42.519 --> 05:44.754
Honestly, I'm fine.
It was totally my fault.

05:51.160 --> 05:53.462
That is way too much horse
for that girl.

05:53.529 --> 05:55.097
I bought him for her specifically.

05:55.164 --> 05:57.967
She has to learn how to
handle horses like this.

05:58.034 --> 05:59.167
She's just not ready.

05:59.235 --> 06:02.203
I don't think I can help you.

06:02.270 --> 06:04.872
Are you actually turning
this job down?

06:04.940 --> 06:06.207
I guess I am.

06:07.142 --> 06:10.377
Well, that's not very good
for her career...

06:10.445 --> 06:11.512
Or yours.

06:20.135 --> 06:24.925
